<subSubSection box="[189,752,590,617]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="16.[136,1452,158,1193]" box="[189,752,590,617]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,748,590,616]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">
Subtribe 
<taxonomicName authority="Britton &amp; Rose (1920)" authorityName="Britton &amp; Rose" authorityYear="1920" box="[300,748,590,616]" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Trichocereinae">
Trichocereinae 
<bibRefCitation author="Britton, N. L. &amp; Rose, J. N." box="[485,748,590,616]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" refId="ref16302" refString="Britton, N. L. &amp; Rose, J. N. (1920) The Cactaceae, vol. 3. Washington, Carnegie Institution, 248 pp." type="book" year="1920">Britton &amp; Rose (1920)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="95" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[136,1452,158,1193]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">
—Most of the genera in Subtribe 
<taxonomicName box="[1131,1286,590,616]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Trichocereine">Trichocereine</taxonomicName>
are also found in the traditional concept “Trichocereae” and the same applies to all the five Chilean genera [
<taxonomicName authority="Backeb." authorityName="Backeb." box="[1185,1448,626,652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Haageocereus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1185,1346,627,652]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">Haageocereus</emphasis>
Backeb.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Backeb." authorityName="Backeb." box="[136,356,662,688]" class="Gastropoda" family="Assimineidae" genus="Leucostele" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[136,256,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">Leucostele</emphasis>
Backeb.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Britton &amp; Rose, Oreocereus (A. Berger) Riccob., and Soehrensia Backeb." box="[367,1275,662,689]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Lobivia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[367,453,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">Lobivia</emphasis>
Britton &amp; Rose, 
<emphasis box="[642,771,663,689]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">Oreocereus</emphasis>
(A.Berger) Riccob., and 
<emphasis box="[1051,1174,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">Soehrensia</emphasis>
Backeb.
</taxonomicName>
] in the Subtribe 
<taxonomicName box="[136,307,698,724]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Trichocereinae">Trichocereinae</taxonomicName>
. Based on DNA sequences and a broad sampling, Schlumperger &amp; Renner (2012) showed that the large genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Zucc." authorityName="Zucc." box="[273,467,734,761]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Echinopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[273,396,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">Echinopsis</emphasis>
Zucc.
</taxonomicName>
is polyphyletic. Consequently, many former segregate genera were reinstalled, and the names of the Chilean taxa needed to be changed from 
<taxonomicName box="[736,859,770,796]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Echinopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[736,859,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">Echinopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[865,898,770,796]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
into 
<taxonomicName authority="Backeb." authorityName="Backeb." box="[953,1173,770,796]" class="Gastropoda" family="Assimineidae" genus="Leucostele" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[953,1073,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">Leucostele</emphasis>
Backeb.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Britton &amp; Rose, and Soehrensia Backeb. (Schlumpberger 2012)" authorityName="Britton &amp; Rose, and Soehrensia Backeb. (Schlumpberger" authorityYear="2012" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Lobivia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1183,1269,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">Lobivia</emphasis>
Britton &amp; Rose, and 
<emphasis box="[184,307,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">Soehrensia</emphasis>
Backeb. (Schlumpberger 2012)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hunt, D." box="[681,812,806,833]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" pagination="3 - 4" refId="ref17115" refString="Hunt, D. (2012) Tricky Trichos. Cactaceae Systematics Initiatives 28: 3 - 4." type="journal article" year="2012">Hunt (2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hunt, D." box="[824,883,806,832]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" refId="ref17134" refString="Hunt, D. (2016) CITES Cactaceae Checklist Third Edition. Milborne Port, Remous Limited, 175 pp." type="book" year="2016">2016</bibRefCitation>
, see 
<tableCitation box="[937,1022,806,832]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="4.[136,224,159,183]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="TABLE 2 (1/4). Updated checklist of Chilean genera and species in comparison with works by Hunt et al. (2006, 2013, 2016) and Rodríguez et al. (2018). Names in bold highlight differences among the works. Symbols: - = new taxa backed by molecular data but not accepted by Hunt et al. (2006, 2013, 2016) and Rodríguez et al. (2018); numbers in brackets () = supported by following relevant studies: 1 = Larridon et al. (2015), 2 = Ritz et al. (2012); 3 = Guerrero et al. (2019b); 4a= Larridon et al. (2018a); 4b = Larridon et al. (2018b), 5a = Schlumpberger &amp; Renner (2012); 5b = Schlumpberger (2012); 6 = Nyffeler &amp; Eggli (2010); 7 = Wallace &amp; Dickie (2001); 8 = Griffith &amp; Porter (2009); 9 = Nyffeler 2002; 10 = Edwards et al. 2005; 11 = Ritz et al. 2007; 12 = Lendel 2006; 13 = Hernández-Hernández et al. 2011; 14= Walter (2011); 15 = Eggli &amp; Walter (2012); 16 = Wilson (2016); 17 = Vergara (2011, cited in Guerrero et al. 2019b); 18 = Walter (2019); 19 = Guerrero, unpublished data; 20 = Merklinger et al. (2021); * = taxa “alternatively” accepted by Hunt (2016). Taxa in italics not still included in the sampling of relevant molecular studies." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF6F6659FFE2FFB0FF30068EFD72FE38" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" tableUuid="DF6F6659FFE2FFB0FF30068EFD72FE38">Table 2</tableCitation>
), accepted Schlumperger’s concept as “alternative”, while 
<bibRefCitation author="Rodriguez, R. &amp; Marticorena, C. &amp; Alarcon, D. &amp; Baeza, C. &amp; Cavieres, V. &amp; Finot, L. &amp; Fuentes, N. &amp; Kiessling, A. &amp; Mihoc, M. &amp; Pauchard, A. &amp; Ruiz, E. &amp; Sanchez, P. &amp; Marticorena, A." box="[362,624,842,868]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" pagination="1 - 430" refId="ref18598" refString="Rodriguez, R., Marticorena, C., Alarcon, D., Baeza, C., Cavieres, V., Finot, L., Fuentes, N., Kiessling, A., Mihoc, M., Pauchard, A., Ruiz, E., Sanchez, P. &amp; Marticorena, A. (2018) Catalogo de las plantas vasculares de Chile. Gayana Botanica 75: 1 - 430. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.4067 / S 0717 - 66432018000100001" type="journal article" year="2018">
Rodríguez 
<emphasis box="[486,542,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
still upheld the 
<taxonomicName box="[804,927,842,868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Echinopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[804,927,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">Echinopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[934,967,842,868]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
concept.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[136,1452,158,1193]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">
Concerning the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[446,566,878,904]" class="Gastropoda" family="Assimineidae" genus="Leucostele" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[446,566,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">Leucostele</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the old name 
<taxonomicName authority="Mol." authorityName="Mol." box="[738,1036,878,905]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Macrothricidae" genus="Cactus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coquimbanus">
<emphasis box="[738,973,878,905]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">Cactus coquimbanus</emphasis>
Mol.
</taxonomicName>
has recently been rejected for being ambiguous (
<bibRefCitation author="Eggli, U. &amp; Walter, H. E." box="[276,517,914,940]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" pagination="686 - 687" refId="ref16530" refString="Eggli, U. &amp; Walter, H. E. (2012) Proposal to reject the name Cactus coquimbanus (Cactaceae). Taxon 61: 686 - 687. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / tax. 613024" type="journal article" year="2012">Eggli &amp; Walter 2012</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Wilson, K. L." box="[582,749,914,941]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" pagination="878" refId="ref19377" refString="Wilson, K. L. (2016) Report of the General Committee. Taxon 65: 878. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / 654.15" type="journal article" year="2016">Wilson (2016)</bibRefCitation>
. Consequently, all combinations using this basionym must be abandoned. Among them is “ 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mol.) Schlumpb." authorityName="Schlumpb." baseAuthorityName="Mol." box="[457,931,950,977]" class="Gastropoda" family="Assimineidae" genus="Leucostele" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="coquimbana">
<emphasis box="[457,720,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">Leucostele coquimbana</emphasis>
(Mol.) Schlumpb.
</taxonomicName>
”. 
<collectionCode box="[948,967,950,976]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
new combination of 
<taxonomicName authority="Phil." authorityName="Phil." box="[1200,1447,950,977]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Cereus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nigripilis">
<emphasis box="[1200,1387,950,977]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">Cereus nigripilis</emphasis>
Phil.
</taxonomicName>
, which represents the shrubby columnar plants occurring along the coast from the Coquimbo- to the 
<collectingRegion box="[1263,1452,986,1012]" country="Chile" name="Atacama" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">Atacama Region</collectingRegion>
was recently proposed [
<taxonomicName authority="(Phil.)" baseAuthorityName="Phil." box="[412,726,1022,1049]" class="Gastropoda" family="Assimineidae" genus="Leucostele" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="nigripilis">
<emphasis box="[412,645,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">Leucostele nigripilis</emphasis>
(Phil.)
</taxonomicName>
<collectionCode box="[736,754,1022,1048]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
. 
<collectionCode box="[758,778,1022,1048]" country="Denmark" name="University of Copenhagen" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" type="Herbarium">C</collectionCode>
. 
<collectingRegion box="[792,893,1022,1048]" country="Mexico" name="Guerrero" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">Guerrero</collectingRegion>
&amp; Helmut Walter (see 
<collectingRegion box="[1168,1269,1022,1048]" country="Mexico" name="Guerrero" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">Guerrero</collectingRegion>
&amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Walter, H. E." box="[1311,1451,1022,1048]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" pagination="49 - 56" refId="ref19353" refString="Walter, H. E. (2019) The cacti of the Chilean Patagonia. Cactus World 37: 49 - 56." type="journal article" year="2019">Walter 2019</bibRefCitation>
and 
<tableCitation box="[183,270,1058,1085]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="4.[136,224,159,183]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="TABLE 2 (1/4). Updated checklist of Chilean genera and species in comparison with works by Hunt et al. (2006, 2013, 2016) and Rodríguez et al. (2018). Names in bold highlight differences among the works. Symbols: - = new taxa backed by molecular data but not accepted by Hunt et al. (2006, 2013, 2016) and Rodríguez et al. (2018); numbers in brackets () = supported by following relevant studies: 1 = Larridon et al. (2015), 2 = Ritz et al. (2012); 3 = Guerrero et al. (2019b); 4a= Larridon et al. (2018a); 4b = Larridon et al. (2018b), 5a = Schlumpberger &amp; Renner (2012); 5b = Schlumpberger (2012); 6 = Nyffeler &amp; Eggli (2010); 7 = Wallace &amp; Dickie (2001); 8 = Griffith &amp; Porter (2009); 9 = Nyffeler 2002; 10 = Edwards et al. 2005; 11 = Ritz et al. 2007; 12 = Lendel 2006; 13 = Hernández-Hernández et al. 2011; 14= Walter (2011); 15 = Eggli &amp; Walter (2012); 16 = Wilson (2016); 17 = Vergara (2011, cited in Guerrero et al. 2019b); 18 = Walter (2019); 19 = Guerrero, unpublished data; 20 = Merklinger et al. (2021); * = taxa “alternatively” accepted by Hunt (2016). Taxa in italics not still included in the sampling of relevant molecular studies." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF6F6659FFE2FFB0FF30068EFD72FE38" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" tableUuid="DF6F6659FFE2FFB0FF30068EFD72FE38">Table 2</tableCitation>
)]. Several new taxa in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[643,763,1058,1084]" class="Gastropoda" family="Assimineidae" genus="Leucostele" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[643,763,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">Leucostele</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were also recently proposed in different journals. As none of them had been included in the sampling of a molecular-based study, we decided not to accept them as long as they are supported by molecular phylogenies: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Albesiano) Schlumpb." authorityName="Schlumpb." baseAuthorityName="Albesiano" box="[560,965,1130,1157]" class="Gastropoda" family="Assimineidae" genus="Leucostele" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="faundezii">
<emphasis box="[560,694,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">L. faundezii</emphasis>
(Albesiano) Schlumpb.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Albesiano) Schlumpb." authorityName="Schlumpb." baseAuthorityName="Albesiano" box="[976,1400,1130,1157]" class="Gastropoda" family="Assimineidae" genus="Leucostele" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pectinifera">
<emphasis box="[976,1128,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">L. pectinifera</emphasis>
(Albesiano) Schlumpb.
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Albesiano) Schlumpb. (Korotkova et al. 2021)" box="[136,810,1166,1193]" class="Gastropoda" family="Assimineidae" genus="Leucostele" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="undulosa">
<emphasis box="[136,269,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">L. undulosa</emphasis>
(Albesiano) Schlumpb. (
<bibRefCitation author="Korotkova, N. &amp; Aquino, D. &amp; Arias, S. &amp; Eggli, U. &amp; Franck, A. &amp; Gomez-Hinostrosa, C. &amp; Guerrero, P. C. &amp; Hernandez, H. M. &amp; Kohlbecker, A. &amp; Kohler, M. &amp; Luther, K. &amp; Majure, L. C. &amp; Muller, A. &amp; Metzing, D. &amp; Nyffeler, R. &amp; Sanchez, D. &amp; Schlumpberger, B. &amp; Berendsohn, W. G." box="[549,801,1166,1192]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" pagination="251 - 270" refId="ref17345" refString="Korotkova, N., Aquino, D., Arias, S., Eggli, U., Franck, A., Gomez-Hinostrosa, C., Guerrero, P. C., Hernandez, H. M., Kohlbecker, A., Kohler, M., Luther, K., Majure, L. C., Muller, A., Metzing, D., Nyffeler, R., Sanchez, D., Schlumpberger, B. &amp; Berendsohn, W. G. (2021) Cactaceae at Caryophyllales. org - a dynamic online species-level taxonomic backbone for the family. - Willdenowia 51: 251 - 270. https: // doi. org / 10.3372 / wi. 51.51208" type="journal article" year="2021">
Korotkova 
<emphasis box="[678,734,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
